.TH "vmw_cmdbuf_alloc" 9 "vmw_cmdbuf_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_cmdbuf_alloc \- Allocate a command buffer header complete with command buffer space.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" vmw_cmdbuf_alloc
.BI "(struct vmw_cmdbuf_man *man "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "bool interruptible "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_cmdbuf_header **p_header "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "man" 12
The command buffer manager.
.IP "size" 12
The requested size of the buffer space.
.IP "interruptible" 12
Whether to sleep interruptible while waiting for space.
.IP "p_header" 12
points to a header pointer to populate on successful return.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a pointer to command buffer space if successful. Otherwise
returns an error pointer. The header pointer returned in \fIp_header\fP should
be used for upcoming calls to \fBvmw_cmdbuf_reserve\fP and \fBvmw_cmdbuf_commit\fP.
